description._content: "Wednesday April 11th. The Military Barracks bears the following inscription on the front of the building:- "built 1834, Major Anserdon, K.H. Commandant". This building is surrounded by a 20 foot wall with bastions, or small towers at the four corners, and parts are loop-holed for musketry. The entrance has the usual wide door, or gateway in the center of the wall, flanked on either side by smaller doors, of the same style and character as the Prison Gateway, over which appears the date, 1847. " - Journal of a Trip to Norfolk Island by Frank Walker, R.A.H.S., April, 1917. This image is part of a collection entitled 'Views of Norfolk Island', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel.
